  - elementId: efficiency-chart
    elementType: chart
    bounds: [860, 90, 340, 280]
    type: bar
    data:
      - {model: "Full", memory: 100, time: 100}
      - {model: "Longformer", memory: 42, time: 38}
      - {model: "BigBird", memory: 48, time: 45}
      - {model: "HSA", memory: 28, time: 22}
    x: model
    y: [memory, time]
    names: ["Memory (%)", "Time (%)"]
    colors: ["$secondary", "$primary"]
    options:
      fontFamily: "Arial, Microsoft YaHei"
    legend:
      show: true
      position: top
      fontSize: 11
    yAxis:
      title: "Relative (%)"
      gridLine:
        color: "#F1F5F9"
        style: solid
        width: 1
      label:
        fontSize: 11
        color: "$textLight"
    xAxis:
      label:
        fontSize: 11
        color: "$textLight"

  - elementId: analysis-text
    elementType: text
    bounds: [80, 390, 1120, 120]
    content:
      style: "$body"
      align: [left, top]
      text: |
        <p><strong>Key Findings</strong></p>
        <p style="margin-top:4px">HSA achieves <strong>4.2 F1 improvement</strong> on ArXiv-Summ and <strong>6.8 F1</strong> on PubMed-QA over the strongest baseline (BigBird). Notably, HSA outperforms even Full Attention on PubMed-QA (+6.8), suggesting the hierarchical inductive bias is beneficial for biomedical domain structure. Efficiency gains are substantial: <strong>72% reduction</strong> in memory usage and <strong>78% reduction</strong> in training time versus Full Attention.</p>

  - elementId: ablation-text
    elementType: text
    bounds: [80, 520, 1120, 100]
    content:
      style: "$body"
      align: [left, top]
      text: |
        <p><strong>Ablation Study</strong></p>
        <p style="margin-top:4px">Removing document-level global tokens (-2.1 F1), paragraph-level compression (-1.4 F1), or sentence-level local windows (-1.8 F1) all degrade performance, confirming that each granularity contributes complementary information. The full three-level hierarchy is necessary for optimal results.</p>

  - elementId: source-note
    elementType: text
    bounds: [80, 660, 1000, 20]
    content:
      style: "$footnote"
      align: [left, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>Source: Results averaged over 3 random seeds; 95% CI ±0.8 F1; <a href="https://example.com">Reproducibility repository</a></p>

  - elementId: page-num
    elementType: text
    bounds: [1180, 680, 60, 20]
    content:
      style: "$pageNumber"
      align: [right, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>06</p>
